spanGrp.span: our language was been lost already;
they do not forget our language;
je ka të se je ktö' shewẽ (_)
and so they do not lose it.
jebi ka í të í shewẽ
They say that have not forgotten it.
Jie-wa të í she jie-wa ka wã í shewã-nã
ta jiska ra se je kã' jãrga ra
se yaiwa se se se tsetsegi
all have already lost our language.
todo se je je je-wa të (_) se ktö' shewã'-wã-ka
je-wa (_) (_) keyëge-wa je të se ktö' she-gẽ
and the small kids in some cases cannot speak the language.
ta yabla tsõ yuli-la ra jamẽ (_) ka ĩã mãlela se ktö'ye
We have to teach it to them
so that they can speak it when they grow up, uh…
para ke jie-wa se ktö' sh/ shö-glö mas keyëge (eh) estee
so they do not lose it when they are adults.’
jie-wa deũ keyëge-wa ra jie-wa ka se (m) ktö' shewã-glö-wã
